name: Scyther

attack.name: Energy Loop

name: Shroomish
flavorText: If it senses danger, it scatters spores from the top of its head to protect itself.

attack.name: Double Headbutt

attack.name: Knuckle Impact
attack.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can’t attack.

flavorText: Its flowers give off a relaxing fragrance. The stronger its aroma, the healthier the Roselia is.

name: Roserade

abilities.name: Poison Point
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent’s Pokémon (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: After captivating opponents with its sweet scent, it lashes them with its thorny whips.

attack.name: Bind Down

name: Turtwig

flavorText: Photosynthesis occurs across its body under the sun. The shell on its back is actually hardened soil.

name: Grotle
flavorText: It lives along water in forests. In the daytime, it leaves the forest to sunbathe its treed shell.

attack.name: Ramming Shell
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, this Pokémon takes 20 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: It scatters cotton all over the place as a prank. If it gets wet, it’ll become too heavy to move and have no choice but to answer for its mischief.

attack.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may heal all damage from your Active Grass Pokémon. If you healed any damage in this way, discard all Energy from that Pokémon.

flavorText: Sawsbuck in their Autumn Form are known for having very short tempers. The males fight each other incessantly.

attack.name: Flock

name: Dhelmise

attack.text: If you have any Metal Pokémon on your Bench, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Bramblin
flavorText: Not even Bramblin knows where it is headed as it tumbles across the wilderness, blown by the wind. It loathes getting wet.

name: Brambleghast

abilities.name: Resilient Soul

flavorText: Brambleghast wanders around arid regions. On rare occasions, mass outbreaks of these Pokémon will bury an entire town.

attack.name: Powerful Needles

attack.name: Slight Intrusion

attack.name: Psychic
attack.text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

attack.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can’t attack.

attack.name: Inferno Onrush
attack.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

attack.name: Roasting Heat

name: Victini
flavorText: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

attack.name: Singe Off
attack.text: Discard a Special Energy from your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

attack.name: Licking Flames
attack.text: Flip 3 coins. For each tails, discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Litten

attack.name: Fake Out

attack.name: Blaze Blitz

attack.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attack.name: Powder Snow

attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, the Defending Pokémon can’t attack.

attack.text: If your opponent has any Water Pokémon in play, this attack does 120 more damage.

attack.name: Strong Volt
attack.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

attack.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon is a Psychic Pokémon, this attack does 30 more damage.

attack.name: Double Trick
attack.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

flavorText: While it could use its psychic abilities in battle, this Pokémon prefers to swing its powerful arms around to beat opponents into submission.

attack.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 3 Basic Fighting Energy cards and discard them. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Excadrill

attack.name: Wild Tackle

name: Golett

attack.name: Iron Defense
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent’s next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks.

name: Golurk

attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent’s next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks.

attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon is a Pokémon ex or Pokémon V, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Lycanroc

name: Mudsdale

attack.name: Knock Away

attack.name: Cragalanche

name: Great Tusk
flavorText: Sightings of this Pokémon have occurred in recent years. The name Great Tusk was taken from a creature listed in a certain book.

attack.name: Land Collapse

name: Sandy Shocks

attack.name: Poison Blend
